{
  "bookId": "heshanggong-laozi",
  "num": 48,
  "title": "第四十八章（忘知）",
  "author": "老子",
  "authorId": "Laozi",
  "dynasty": "周",
  "era": "周",
  "genre": "prose",
  "verses": [
    {
      "text": "為學日益，"
    },
    {
      "text": "為道日損。"
    },
    {
      "text": "損之又損，"
    },
    {
      "text": "以至於無為，"
    },
    {
      "text": "無為而無不為。"
    },
    {
      "text": "取天下常以無事，"
    },
    {
      "text": "及其有事，不足以取天下。"
    }
  ],
  "sections": {},
  "annotations": [],
  "layers": {
    "heshanggong": [
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-1",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 0,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "學謂政教禮樂之學也。 日益者，情欲文飾日以益多。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-2",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 1,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "道謂之自然之道也。 日損者，情欲文飾日以消損。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-3",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 2,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 5
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "損情欲也。又損之，所以漸去。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-4",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 3,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 6
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "當恬淡如嬰兒，無所造為也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-5",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 4,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 7
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "情欲斷絕，德於道合，則無所不施，無所不為也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-6",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 5,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 8
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "取，治也。治天下當以無事，不當以勞煩也。",
        "source": "cham"
      },
      {
        "id": "heshanggong-7",
        "range": {
          "type": "range",
          "scope": "verse",
          "verseIndex": 6,
          "start": 0,
          "end": 12
        },
        "kind": "commentary",
        "text": "及其好有事，則政教煩，民不安，故不足以治天下也。",
        "source": "cham"
      }
    ]
  },
